                                <provenance type="found" when="1930">
                                    <p>The altar was found during the excavations of 1930 at
                                        <placeName type="ancientFindspot" ref="https://www.slsgazetteer.org/909" key="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/373778">Cyrene</placeName>:
                                        <rs type="monuList" ref="https://www.slsgazetteer.org/1228">Sanctuary of Apollo</rs>, so-called
                                        <rs type="monuList" ref="https://www.slsgazetteer.org/1366">Agora of the Gods</rs> at its Western end.
                                   </p>
                                </provenance>
                            <provenance type="observed" when="1990">
                                <p>The brazier was taken out and its inscription discovered and studied in 1990 by Cl. Parisi Presicce in the 
                                    <rs type="monuList" ref="https://www.slsgazetteer.org/933">Cyrene Museum</rs>: <rs type="monuList" ref="https://www.slsgazetteer.org/1484">Storeroom of the Italian missions</rs>.</p>
